<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen Discussed With French Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen Discussed With French Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306001094 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network in 
Arabic 2230 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306001094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Royal Highness Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal, foreign 
affairs minister, met Alain Juppe, French foreign affairs 
minister, in Paris yesterday. 
  During the meeting, the developments of the situation in 
Yemen were discussed, whereby the two sides affirmed the need to 
speed the implementation of the cease-fire in Yemen. 
  Following the meeting, His Highness Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal 
stressed that Paris and Riyadh were in agreement on the priority 
of implementing the Security Council's resolution. 
  His Highness added that the meeting with Juppe also dealt 
with Saudi-French bilateral relations. 
  On his part, the French foreign affairs minister stressed 
that Saudi Arabia and France hoped that the two Yemeni sides 
would, at the earliest moment, adhere to the cease-fire 
stipulated by the UN Security Council's resolution No. 924. 

</TEXT>

