<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Examines Yemen Crisis at Weekly Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Examines Yemen Crisis at Weekly Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006193494 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 1725 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Jeddah, 20 Jun -- The Council of Ministers held 
its weekly meeting today in al-Salam Palace in Jeddah under the 
chairmanship of His Royal Highness Prince Sultan 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, second deputy prime minister, minister of 
defense and aviation, and inspector-general. 
  After the meeting, the Information Minister 'Ali al-Sha'ir 
made a statement to SPA in which he said: After a quick review 
of a report on the most significant political and military 
events in the Arab region, the council heard a comprehensive 
explanation by his royal highness the second deputy prime 
minister on some topics in the report, primary among which are 
events on the Yemeni scene. In this context, the information 
minister said: The council followed with great interest the 
continuous efforts made by the Security Council through UN Envoy 
Lakhdar Brahimi, who still continues his attempts to secure an 
implementation of Resolution No. 924 calling for a cease-fire 
throughout all Yemeni territory in order to end the bloodshed 
and save the lives of the sons of fraternal Yemen. [passage 
omitted] 
  The information minister concluded his statement by saying 
that the cabinet discussed the items on the agenda and issued 
the following resolution: 
  Approving negotiations with the Russian Federation with a 
view to reaching an agreement on joint cooperation between the 
two countries in various fields. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

