<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Contract' Reportedly Put Out on Opposition Figure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Contract' Reportedly Put Out on Opposition Figure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2006103794 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 20 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2006103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Saudi security agencies have put out a contract on 
the opposition figure Shaykh Usamah Bin-Ladin. They assigned 
the job to an assassination group, led by a hit man from an Arab 
country. 
  The London-based Committee for the Defense of (Saudi) 
Legitimate Rights said that Saudi Arabia, which has paid a huge 
sum to this gang, is apparently trying to stay away from the 
assassination attempt for domestic reasons connected with tribal 
vendettas and external reasons connected with the image of Saudi 
Arabia abroad. 
  In a related development, Usamah's mother was surprised when 
a police officer prevented her from boarding a plane that was 
about to take off, even though she had completed airport 
formalities on her way to be treated abroad from an incurable 
disease. 

</TEXT>

