<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Iryani Leaves for Talks With Butrus-Ghali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Iryani Leaves for Talks With Butrus-Ghali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2306093494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0800 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2306093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, minister of 
planning and development, left Sanaa for the United States today 
on a working visit of several days. In a statement to the 
Yemeni News Agency, SABA', the minister noted that, during his 
New York visit, he will meet with Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali, 
secretary general of the United Nations, and brother Lakhdar 
Brahimi, envoy of the UN secretary general, to follow up the 
situation in the Republic of Yemen. 
  Al-Iryani added he will then head for Washington to hold 
meetings and talks with officials at the U.S. Department of 
State to discuss bilateral relations. The minister of planning 
and development said he will discuss, during the visit, ways to 
implement Security Council Resolution 924 under Yemeni unity and 
constitutional legitimacy. He will also explain to UN and U.S. 
officials the violations committed by rebels against 
international legitimacy represented by Security Council 
Resolution 924 in an attempt to circumvent the content of the 
resolution to achieve illegitimate objectives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

