<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Salih Briefs Party Leaders on Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Salih Briefs Party Leaders on Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2206185494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2206185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, today met with leaders and 
representatives of political parties and organizations. He 
briefed them on the latest developments in the situation on the 
national, political, and military fronts. He also briefed them 
on the efforts that have been exerted on the foreign level and 
the nature of the talks that have been held with Lakhdar 
Brahimi, envoy of the UN secretary general. 
  The brother president explained that from the outset, our 
country stressed its abidance by UN Security Council Resolution 
No. 924 and its full readiness to implement it. He added that 
our country proposed five cease-fire initiatives to stop Yemeni 
bloodshed and to give those who have been misled a chance to 
join the ranks of unity and legitimacy. 
  The brother president said the leaders of rebellion and 
secession insisted on (?rejecting) all initiatives because the 
UN Security Council resolution did not serve their inhuman and 
anti-unity objectives. They continued to violate the cease-fire 
and to escalate the military situation in order to prolong the 
war and internationalize the Yemeni issue. 
  The brother president praised the political parties and 
organizations for their principled stand on the challenges 
facing national unity at this delicate phase in the history of 
the homeland. He also praised their commitment to national 
issues. He said that the challenges facing the homeland have 
proven the credibility of the people's national stands and 
cohesion as they confront the enemies of the homeland, unity, 
and democracy. He stressed that our country will continue to 
adhere to the option of unity and democracy as an irreversible 
option to build a modern Yemen based on the principles of 
political and party pluralism, economic freedom, the freedom of 
expression, respect for human rights, developed local 
government, and progress and comprehensive development 
throughout Yemen. 
  The brother president indicated that the next phase requires 
cooperation and cohesion among our people to rebuild what the 
treasonous, rebellious gang has destroyed in all fields, 
starting with supporting the families of the martyrs' and 
victims in all governorates. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

