<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden: Enemy Advances Checked; Battles Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden: Enemy Advances Checked; Battles Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2206204094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2206204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen Defense Ministry has stated the following: The forces of 
the ruling military regime in Sanaa today continued their 
desperate offensive attempts to advance in the direction of the 
capital, Aden. At the same time, they continued their rocket, 
air, and artillery shelling of residential quarters and economic 
and service installations in Aden, while our Armed Forces 
confronted them bravely. 
  Our Armed Forces prevented any advances by the enemy, and 
forced him to withdraw and abandon numerous occupied positions. 
They also inflicted further human and material losses on him. 
The enemy losses were as follows: 20 tanks, 10 crews members 
[atqum], five Katyusha rocket launching vehicles, a MiG-21 jet, 
and hundreds of killed and wounded. 
  In Shabwah Governorate, our forces, in close coordination 
with the tribes of Shabwah and popular resistance detachments, 
continued liquidating scattered remnants and pockets of the 
forces of the ruling military regime in Sanaa. Our forces 
managed to capture (al-Qat) Camp, two trucks loaded with 
ammunition, and supply goods. 
  In Ma'rib Governorate, popular resistance detachments 
destroyed a meeting site for leaders and supporters of the 
military regime in Sanaa. In Wadi (Tubah), two troop trucks 
were completely destroyed. Battles are still continuing on all 
combat fronts between our defending forces and the (?oppressive) 
and aggressive forces of the ruling military regime in Sanaa. 
Victory is our ally, God willing. 

</TEXT>

