<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern Plane Shot Down </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Plane Shot Down </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206171194 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1630 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 22 June, KUNA -- At noon today, southern 
antiaircraft defenses shot down a northern warplane that was 
raiding Aden. A southern military source has said that the 
aircraft was trying to raid the television station, which is 
situated in the mountainous al-Tawahi region. 
  He added that the northern warplanes conducted more raids on 
Aden a few hours after the airport was the target of a Katyusha 
barrage from a northern military launcher. He pointed out that 
the shells did not hit the airport, but a number of ordinary 
houses were damaged instead. The source did not give any 
details on the damage of the missile barrage. 
  KUNA's correspondent, however, saw a number of fire engines 
heading to the areas close to the airport, which is situated in 
the Khur Maksar district in the heart of the city of Aden. 

</TEXT>

