<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Killed, 39 Wounded in Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Killed, 39 Wounded in Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306064894 Paris AFP in English 0445 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 23 (AFP) -- The bombardment of 
Aden by northern forces resumed at dawn Thursday, with shells 
and missiles wounding 11 civilians, the city's main hospital 
said. 
  As artillery duels between north and south continued near 
Aden, three southern soldiers were reported killed and 28 
wounded. Nine residents of the northern district of Shaykh 
'Uthman were wounded by shells falling on the city itself at the 
rate of two or three a minute, mainly landing near the airport, 
the al-Jumhuriyah hospital said. 
  A southern military spokesman said three missiles were fired 
at Aden, two of which were brought down by anti-aircraft fire. 
The third exploded on the hills overlooking the town, near the 
al-Tawahi district. The hospital said two women were wounded in 
the blast, which badly damaged a number of wooden homes in the 
district. 

</TEXT>

