<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Death Toll Updated to 12 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Death Toll Updated to 12 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306090994 Paris AFP in English 0816 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 23 (AFP) -- A heavy northern 
bombardment of this southern city killed 12 civilians and 
wounded 98 on Thursday as shells slammed into the fish market 
and other central sites, hospital officials said. 
  Wounded soldiers were meanwhile pouring into military 
hospitals from frontlines 20 kilometres (12 miles) from the city 
where dawn artillery duels left three southern troops dead and 
28 wounded, the officials said. 
  Two shells hit the fish market at al-Mu'alla on the sea 
front, killing two people and wounded around a dozen others, 
several seriously. A salvo of Kaytusha rockets destroyed five 
houses in the working class district of al-Mansurah. Shells also 
hit the Khormaksar district near the airport and northern 
suburbs near the front. 
  A southern military spokesman said three missiles were also 
fired at Aden, two of which were brought down by anti-aircraft 
fire. The third exploded on the hills overlooking the town, 
injuring two women and damaging wooden houses. 
  Northern forces loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 
southerners backing his rival 'Ali Salim al-Bid have been locked 
in civil war for almost two months. 

</TEXT>

