<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets Russian Intelligence Chief Primakov </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Meets Russian Intelligence Chief Primakov </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206175794 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President 'Arafat, head of the State of Palestine 
and chairman of the PLO's Executive Committee, today received 
Yevgeniy Primakov, director of foreign intelligence of the 
Russian Federation, and the delegation accompanying him. 
  A full review was made of: developments in the Palestinian 
arena, particularly in the occupied territories; the results 
thus far of the implementation of the agreement on Palestinian 
self-rule in Gaza and Jericho as a means of strengthening the 
pillars of the Palestinian national authority; the need for the 
withdrawal of Israeli troops from the self-rule territories; as 
well as the requirements for consolidating the structures of the 
national authority. 
  President 'Arafat expressed gratitude for Russia's firm 
stance in its capacity as one of the cosponsors of the Middle 
East peace process, assessed highly the close relations between 
Russia and Palestine, and stressed the need for strengthening 
and developing them. 
  During the meeting, Primakov reaffirmed his country's firm 
stance in supporting the peace process and in firmly 
establishing the basis and structures of the Palestinian 
National Authority. 

</TEXT>

