<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Party Official Meets DFLP's Hawatimah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Party Official Meets DFLP's Hawatimah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2206172294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2206172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Viktor Antilov, secretary general of the Russian 
Communist Workers Party [title as heard], has stressed that the 
Russian people are standing alongside the Palestinian people in 
their struggle to regain their rights to self-determination, the 
establishment of an independent Palestinian state, and 
repatriation. He added that the Russian people also support 
peace in accordance with the resolutions of international 
legitimacy. 
  During a meeting with Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general of 
the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP], 
Antilov also asserted that the people of Russia, as well as its 
democratic and communist nationalist forces, support the 
Palestinian people and the Arabs, and that the Russian people 
will not remain silent on the expansionist Israeli plans. 
  For his part, Hawatimah asserted that the Oslo-Cairo 
agreement is doomed to failure because it does not meet the 
minimum requirements of a peace settlement according to the 
resolutions of international legitimacy and also because the 
Israeli occupation and settlements continue to exist in Gaza and 
Jericho, as do the acts of bloody repression throughout the 
occupied territories. 

</TEXT>

