  [Text] Cairo, 22 Jun (MENA) -- President Husni Mubarak 
this morning received Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan, who 
is currently visiting Cairo. The meeting was attended by Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa; Ambassador Mushirah Khattab, Egypt's 
ambassador to Slovakia; Ambassador Jan Borieh [name as 
transliterated], Slovakia's ambassador in Cairo; and Mr. Ivan 
Borkosh, director of the Middle East desk at the Slovak Foreign 
Ministry [name and title as received]. 
  Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan stated after the 
meeting 
that he is very happy that President Mubarak received him today 
at the beginning of his visit to Egypt. He said he held 
fruitful discussions with the president regarding the 
possibilities and means of bolstering cooperation between Egypt 
and Slovakia. 
  He added that we will exploit the good political intentions 
of both sides to strengthen and bolster this cooperation. 
  He said it was a pleasure to convey to President Mubarak the 
invitation from the Slovak president to officially visit our 
country. The president has accepted the invitation and the date 
will be fixed at the appropriate time. 
  The Slovak foreign minister concluded his statement by 
expressing his hopes that the discussions he held with President 
Mubarak today would yield some positive results in future 
relations between Egypt and Slovakia. He noted that his 
discussions with the president today on this topic were very 
encouraging. 
  The Slovak foreign minister arrived in Cairo yesterday 
evening on a visit to last several days. 

