<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Delegation's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Delegation's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406055594 Paris AFP in English 2358 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2406055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, June 24 (AFP) -- A north Yemeni parliamentary 
delegation, seeking support for north Yemen's campaign against 
southern secessionists, met here Thursday [23 June] with PLO 
Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, official sources said. 
  The Palestine Liberation Organization leader stressed the 
need to "continue efforts to reach a just solution that takes 
into account the interests of the Yemeni people," the 
Palestinian news agency WAFA reported. 
  The Yemeni delegation, which also met with Tunisian 
parliamentary leaders and members of legal opposition groups, 
accused Saudi Arabia of supplying arms to southern forces, 
according to diplomatic forces. 
  Civil war erupted in Yemen on May 5 in the midst of a 
political dispute between northern and southern leaders on the 
administration of the country. The south proclaimed itself a 
separate state on May 21. 
  Southern representatives are also touring north Africa. A 
spokesman for the breakaway Yemen Democratic Republic earlier 
Thursday appealed to the international community to "impose a 
ceasefire by force." 
  The Tunisian government has expressed concern at the 
deteriorating situation in Yemen but has not taken sides in the 
conflict. 

</TEXT>

