<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suspects in Hamas Member's Murder Under Investigation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suspects in Hamas Member's Murder Under Investigation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406074894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0658 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2406074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza, 24 Jun (MENA) -- Counselor Khalid al-Qidrah, 
public prosecutor of the Palestinian National Authority, has 
said that suspects in the murder of Nasir Salluhah, an activist 
in the Hamas Movement who was kidnapped two days ago and whose 
body was found in Bayt Lahiyah in northern Gaza, are currently 
under investigation. 
  In a statement to MENA, he affirmed that if the involvement 
of one or all the suspects in murdering Salluhah is proved, they 
will be tried under the standing Palestinian laws. 
  He said that investigation and speedy trial procedures will 
be carried out without violating legal requirements. 
  Salluhah's funeral is scheduled to take place after today's 
Friday prayer. In addition to Hamas leaders, representatives of 
all Palestinian organizations and the Palestinian National 
Authority will take part in the procession. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

