<H4>    Attacks Disrupt Tamanrasset Supplies </H4>

<F P=102> LD2306143194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] National Highway One between In Salah and 
Tamanrasset was the scene of a series of armed attacks during 
the last few months. The attacks were carried out by gangs 
against trucks belonging to the National Road Haulage Company. 
Faced with such a situation the lorries of the aforementioned 
company did not have any other solution but to cut short their 
journey at In Salah, thus starving the region from being 
supplied with most commodities. 
  In an attempt to contain the situation, the local 
authorities 
at Tamanrasset have taken a number of security measures. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

