<H3> <TI>   New Islamist Group Active on Afghan-Pakistan Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Islamist Group Active on Afghan-Pakistan Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306184194 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 15 Jun 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Political Week" section] </F>
  [Text] A new Islamist organization calling itself the 
"Caliphate Group" has recently appeared. The organization, 
which espouses the concept of repudiation and accuses all 
existing Islamic societies and countries of apostasy, is 
operating in tribal territories adjacent to the Pakistani-Afghan 
border. It advocates the restoration of the caliphate under the 
leadership of the group's chief. The membership of the new 
organization comprises Egyptian, Sudanese, Jordanian, and 
Algerian nationals. The leader of the group is an Arab 
millionaire of Palestinian extraction called Abu-'Uthman. He 
considers himself an extension of Shukri Mustafa, leader of the 
Repudation and Renunciation group. 
  Last week the Pakistani authorities asked the group's 
leading 
members to leave Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

