<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Offer Copies of Koran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To Offer Copies of Koran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2406100194 Baghdad AL-QADISIYAH in Arabic 18 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN2406100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-QADISIYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Awqaf and Religious Affairs has 
completed the printing of 60,000 copies of the Holy Koran. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Mun'im Ahmad Salih, minister of awqaf and 
religious affairs, has explained that the new edition is similar 
to the one which was printed in Germany in 1980 in three sizes. 
  The minister added that the Holy Book will be of medium size 
and will be offered to citizens as part of the faith campaign 
led by the struggler leader Saddam Husayn. He said the ministry 
will print another 15,000 copies in the next few weeks in the 
form of sections of the Holy Koran to be used in the mosque 
religious courses held throughout the country during the summer 
holidays. 

</TEXT>

