<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   RCC Decrees New Law on Wife's Legal Separation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RCC Decrees New Law on Wife's Legal Separation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2206164494 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 13 Jun 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> JN2206164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-THAWRAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Revolution Command Council has decided to grant 
the wife of a man who is officially declared missing, the right 
to separate from her husband after four years. 
  This came in a law the Council issued amending Personal 
Status Law No. 188 of 1959. The following is text of the law: 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Republic of Iraq, 
  In the name of the people, 
  Revolution Command Council Decision No. 62, dated 26 Dhu al- 
Hijjah 1414 Hegira corresponding to 6 June 1994: 
  In accordance with the provisions of Paragraph 1 of Article 
42 of the Constitution, the Revolution Command Council decided 
to issue the following law: 
  Law No. (8) of 1994: 
  Law Amending Personal Status Law No. 188 of 1959. 
  Article 1: The following paragraph shall be added to Article 
43 of Personal Status Law No. 188 of 1959 so that it shall 
become the fourth paragraph of that article: 
  Fourth: 1. The wife of a man who is officially proven to be 
missing may apply to the court for a separation from her husband 
after the lapse of four years since he was discovered to be 
missing. The court shall ascertain that the husband has 
continued to be missing in the same way in which he was proven 
missing and then issue its verdict on separation. 
  2. Following the issuance of the separation verdict, the 
wife 
of the missing husband shall observe 'iddah [the legal period of 
waiting before a divorced or widowed Muslim woman can remarry 
under Islamic law] for four months and 10 days. 
  3. If the missing husband returns, the marriage shall 
continue unless the wife has already remarried. In this case, 
the second husband shall be considered as having entered into 
marriage without true knowledge that the first husband is still 
living. 
  Article 2: This law shall be implemented as of the date of 
its issuance in the OFFICIAL GAZETTE. 
  [Signed] Saddam Husayn, chairman of the Revolution Command 
Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

