<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Orders 300-Percent Pay Bonus for Brain Surgeons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Orders 300-Percent Pay Bonus for Brain Surgeons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2106130494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2106130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn has ordered that 
brain and nervous system surgeons be granted monthly allowances 
equal to 300 percent of their total monthly salaries. This has 
been announced to the Iraqi News Agency by Health Minister Dr. 
Umid Midhat Mubarak. He said the leader president has also 
ordered that brain and nervous system surgical operations 
conducted at the Health Ministry's hospitals be excluded from 
the current charge rates. He added that this generous gesture 
by leader President Saddam Husayn reflects appreciation and 
support for this scientific specialization, which requires 
meticulous precision and extreme and distinguished care for 
brain and nervous system patients. He said that this generous 
gesture will encourage this specialization, which is an 
important lifesaving specializations. 

</TEXT>

