</HEADER>

<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran's Embassy Denies Involvement in Arms Cache </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iran's Embassy Denies Involvement in Arms Cache </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306135094 Rabat MAP in English 1315 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabat, June 23 (MAP) -- Iran's Embassy here denied 
Thursday involvement in the arms seized lately by Moroccan 
police and which were destined to the Algerian banned Islamic 
Salvation Front (FIS). 
  The Government of Iran has nothing to do with the arms case, 
the Iranian Embassy said noting that Iran in line with its 
foreign policy principles does not interfere in domestic affairs 
of other countries. 
  An eight-member ring (including six Moroccans and two 
Moroccans) [as received] were dismantled lately by Moroccan 
police while attempting to smuggle arms purchased in Europe to 
FIS via Morocco. 
  The ring members were sentenced to imprisonment terms 
varying 
from 5 to 20 years. 

</TEXT>

