<H3> <TI>   President Ben Ali Receives PRC Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Ben Ali Receives PRC Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306151894 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] At the Carthage Palace this morning President 
Zine El Abidine Ben Ali received Luo Gan, state councillor and 
secretary-general of the PRC State Council, in the presence of 
Foreign Minister Habib Ben Yahia and An Huihou, the PRC 
ambassador to Tunis. 
  Luo Gan said that his talks with the president were held in 
an atmosphere exemplifying the sentiments of Tunisian-Chinese 
friendship and cordiality. He added that relations between 
Tunisia and China have always been good and that the exchange of 
visits between high level officials and bilateral cooperation in 
various fields continues. [passage omitted] 
  The Chinese state councillor pointed out that Tunisia and 
China are currently carrying out a process of reform and 
transformation which would provide extensive fields from which 
the two countries can benefit. 
  At the end of his statement he said: We hope that the 
friendly Tunisian people will achieve further great successes 
under the leadership of President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali. 

