<H3> <TI>   Yi'UD Approves Opening of Coalition Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yi'UD Approves Opening of Coalition Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2206051794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 22 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2206051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The YI'UD [Independent and Democratic Israel] 
party's council has given its backing to negotiations with Labor 
to enter the coalition. Any agreement will be brought before 
the council. 
  Meanwhile, Tzomet leader Refa'el Eytan said he believes that 
there will be legal complications with YI'UD joining the 
coalition. He said he was not sure whether Gonen Segev could 
serve as a minister or Alex Goldfarb as a deputy minister. A 
Qol Yisra'el reporter says the attorney general believes there 
is no legal problem with Gonen Segev serving as a minister, 
while the prime minister's legal adviser believes there is no 
possibility of appointing someone from a breakaway faction to 
the post of minister. 

</TEXT>

