<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Mashhad Bombing Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to Mashhad Bombing Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Velayati Urges Action Against MKO </H4>

<F P=102> LD2306194994 Tehran IRNA in English 1609 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shrine Abu Dhabi (UAE), June 23, IRNA -- The Islamic 
Republic of Iran on Thursday [23 June] urged the Organization of 
the Islamic Conference (OIC) [ICO] to condemn Monday's [20 June] 
bomb blast at the holy shrine of Imam Reza (as) [expansion 
unknown] in Mashhad and take serious measures against the 
terrorist Mojahedin-E Khalq group. 
  Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati, whose official noted 
that the Mojahedin-E Khalq outfit (MKO) was behind the crime. 
[sentence as received] The noted [as received], handed to the 
OIC secretariate in Jeddah, said the terrorist MKO was 
responsible for the bomb blast at the Imam Reza (as) shrine on 
Ashura (martyrdom anniversary of Imam Hussein) which killed tens 
of pilgrims and wounded scores of others. 
  Calling the OIC to step up campaign against terrorism 
through 
coordinated measures by its members, Velayati said the 
organization should take a firm position against terrorism. 
  His note stressed that the OIC members should not let the 
sanctity of the holy places in Bosnia and Palestine to be 
desecrated. 
  Monday's bomb explosion has claimed the lives of at least 26 
mourners of Imam Hussein and injured 170 others besides damaging 
the centuries old art embellishment at the shrine. 

</TEXT>

