<H4>    Delegation Postpones Baghdad Trip </H4>

<F P=102> LD2306184994 Tehran IRNA in English 1758 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 23, IRNA -- A scheduled visit to 
Baghdad this Saturday [25 June] of an Iranian foreign ministry 
delegation has been postponed without indefinitely. [sentence as 
received] 
  The postponement, according to a foreign ministry spokesman 
here tonight, is due to the terrorist bomb blast at the holy 
shrine of Imam Reza (as) in Mashhad on Monday last that took the 
lives of 26 mourners on the day of Ashura (martyrdom anniversary 
of Imam Hussein) and injured about 170 others. 
  The terrorist Mujahidden Khalq outfit (MKO) has been held 
responsible for the blast. 
  The visit to Baghdad was within the framework of pending 
matters between Tehran and Baghdad. 

</TEXT>

