<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities To Launch Kashmir `Action Plan' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities To Launch Kashmir `Action Plan' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2406052094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2406052094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An action plan is to be launched in Jammu and 
Kashmir for improving the law and order situation. The BSF 
[Border Security Force], CRPF [Central Reserve Police Force], 
and the Jammu and Kashmir Police will coordinate in its 
implementation. The plan will have both short-term and 
long-term perspectives. 
  The minister of state for home, Rajesh Pilot, discussed the 
details at a meeting he had with the minister of state for 
defense, Mr. Mallikarjun, in New Delhi yesterday. They reviewed 
the steps being taken to deal with the situation in Jammu and 
Kashmir, particularly in Doda District. The secretaries of home 
and defense, the director generals of BSF and CRPF, and senior 
Army and Home Ministry officials attended the discussions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

