<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Weekly Reports Nasrallah-Fadlallah Differences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weekly Reports Nasrallah-Fadlallah Differences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306173394 Beirut AL-SHIRA' in Arabic 20 Jun 94 pp 14-15 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-SHIRA' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report] </F>
  [Excerpts] Differences have emerged between Hizballah 
Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah and Sayyid Muhammad Husayn 
Fadlallah. The differences came into the open when Hizballah 
held a memorial service in the Southern Suburb for the martyrs 
of the Zionist aggression against Hizballah's camp in 'Ayn 
Kawkab in al-Biqa' and the program did not include a speech by 
Fadlallah. 
  It is worth noting that this was the first time in more than 
10 years that Fadlallah had attended a function without 
delivering a speech. 
  A number of Nasrallah's supporters left a ceremony held by 
the Iranian Embassy on 5 June to mark the anniversary of Imam 
Khomeyni's death when Fadlallah mounted the rostrum to begin a 
speech. 
  It should be recalled that Fadlallah and Nasrallah share the 
loyalty of Hizballah members. But the Hizballah secretary 
general has been trying for more than a year to "purge" the 
party's ranks of the supporters of Fadlallah and the former 
Hizballah secretary general Shaykh Subhi al-Tufayli. 
  Within this framework, Nasrallah has been having his 
supporters distribute a book of remarks about Fadlallah's 
course. He has also been telling his supporters that Shaykh 
Subhi al-Tufayli is responsible for the clashes that took place 
between Hizballah and the Amal Movement. [passage omitted] 
  Nasrallah is currently facing problems with many Iranian 
parties because of the many setbacks Hizballah has suffered 
since Nasrallah assumed the post of secretary general. These 
setbacks--which he suffered among the Shi'ah scholars, party 
members, and the general public--recently forced him to expel 
more than 250 party members for various reasons. 

</TEXT>

