<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets With Yemeni Parliamentarians in Tunis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Meets With Yemeni Parliamentarians in Tunis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306181494 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The brother president, Yasir 'Arafat, met in Tunis 
this morning with His Excellency Yemeni Deputy Parliament 
Speaker 'Abd-al-Wahab Mahmud and the delegation accompanying 
him. His Excellency 'Abd-al-Wahab briefed the brother president 
on the latest situation and the seriousness of the fast-moving 
and delicate developments which concern Yemen and its fraternal 
people. 
  President 'Arafat stressed the importance of continuing 
efforts to find a just solution which would safeguard the 
interest of the fraternal Yemeni people and their effective role 
as one of the pillars of our Arab nation in its endeavour toward 
a better future. 
  His Excellency 'Abd-al-Wahab Mahmud conveyed an important 
message from Yemen's Parliament Speaker Shaykh 'Abdallah 
al-Ahmar to the brother president, Yasir 'Arafat. The meeting 
was attended by his excellency the Yemeni ambassador to Tunisia. 

</TEXT>

