<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kidnapped UK Nationals Released in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kidnapped UK Nationals Released in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306155194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the Kashmir Valley, the two Britishers -- Kim 
Housego and Mr. David Mackie -- kidnapped by the militants have 
been released after 17 days of captivity. The two were released 
unconditionally today in the jungles of Pahalgam. Later, they 
were brought to Srinagar where they were handed over to the 
first secretary of the British High Commission in India. The 
two Britishers were kidnapped on the 7th of this month from 
Kharo in Pahalgam by a militant outfit, Harkatul Ansar. 
  Talking to AIR [All India Radio] correspondent in Srinagar 
after their release, Kim Housego and David Mackie said they did 
not know the exact location where they were kept. They were 
taken from place to place during their 17-day ordeal. 
  The British foreign secretary, Mr. Douglas Hurd, has 
welcomed 
the release of the two Britons. In a statement in London, he 
thanked the Government of India and others who helped their 
release. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-37836 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes122_w_94001" </HT>


