<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Envoy Denies Weapons Supplied to Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Envoy Denies Weapons Supplied to Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306111294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1045 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 23 Jun (MENA) -- Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today received Russian 
Ambassador Vladimir Polyakov. 
  The ambassador said later that on the instructions of the 
Russian leadership he had requested a meeting with the League's 
secretary general to exchange views on the latest developments 
in Yemen. 
  He pointed out that Russia and the League are cooperating 
and 
coordinating their stance on resolving the Yemeni crisis, noting 
that this cooperation takes a diplomatic and political form. 
  The Russian ambassador explained that when the war broke 
out, 
his country appealed to the warring parties in Yemen to stop 
fighting and initiate a dialogue to solve their problems. 
  Polyakov pointed out that Russia's recognition of south 
Yemen 
will depend on the findings included in UN envoy Lakhdar 
Brahimi's report to UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
on the crisis. He denied reports claiming that Russia is 
supplying south Yemen with weapons and assistance in view of the 
close ties linking Moscow with south Yemen in the past. 
  He said Russia halted all weapons supplies to the Yemeni 
parties when the Yemeni crisis began and before fighting broke 
out. 

</TEXT>

