  [Text] Brother President Yasir 'Arafat, president of the 
state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, 
yesterday evening [25 June] received Yahya al-'Arashi, the 
Yemeni minister for civil service and administrative reform, the 
personal envoy of Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. 
  The minister briefed President 'Arafat on the current 
developments in Yemen at all levels, especially the moves being 
made by the Yemeni leadership on the political and diplomatic 
levels to halt the fighting on the basis of the maintenance of 
Yemeni unity. 
  Brother President 'Arafat stressed to the Yemeni minister 
that the Palestinian people and leadership supported the Yemeni 
people and their leadership, and that on our part we were fully 
prepared to exert every effort to halt the fighting and to 
support everything that will benefit the interests of Yemen. 
  The meeting was attended by brothers 'Abbas Zaki and Sakhr 
Habash, members of the Fatah Central Committee, and Muhammad 
Ahmad Haydar, the Yemeni ambassador in Tunis [name and title as 
received]. 

