<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Demands Observers in West Bank By 4 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Demands Observers in West Bank By 4 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2406191694 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 24 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2406191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the 
state of Palestine and PLO Executive Committee chairman, has 
demanded the release of Palestinian prisoners in Israeli jails 
and deployment of international observers in the West Bank and 
Gaza Strip before 4 July in accordance with the agreement signed 
by the PLO and Israel on 4 May. 
  At a meeting last night with ambassadors of the European 
Union states in Tunis, brother President Abu-'Ammar called for 
lifting the restrictions imposed by the Israeli forces on the 
movement of Palestinian officials on the crossings that link the 
West Bank with the Jericho area and Gaza. 
  Informed Palestinian sources said brother President 
Abu-'Ammar emphasized the importance of realizing these demands 
before his return to the Palestinian self-rule areas, and the 
importance of expediting the assistance promised by the donor 
countries for reconstruction and construction in these areas. 
  He said he cannot return to Gaza and Jericho before 
receiving 
this assistance. 
  The source said the ambassadors of the European Union 
promised, at the meeting which was held at their request, to 
convey the demands of brother President Abu-'Ammar regarding 
assistance to their governments. 

</TEXT>

