<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on U.S. Ties, Support for Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister on U.S. Ties, Support for Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2606125094 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2606125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sudanese Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih 
has declared that the government supports Yemeni unity, and 
calls for an end to fighting between brothers to preserve the 
gains and resources of the brotherly Yemeni people. He pointed 
out the need for dialogue to preserve Yemeni unity. In an 
interview with AL-SUDAN AL-HADITH, published today, Dr. 
Abu-Salih added that Sudan is endeavoring to achieve Arab and 
Islamic solidarity and transcend differences, while directing 
its attention against designs aimed at destroying Arab unity. 
He explained that Sudan had taken some earnest steps in this 
respect, through dialogue and adherence to initiatives directed 
at improving relations among Arab states, the Gulf Cooperation 
Council and the Arab Maghreb states. The foreign minister 
declared that a number of western states have begun to make 
contacts with Sudan to restore their previous relations. He 
pointed to the change in relations with the U.S. Government 
after the visit of Madeline Albright. He added that those 
changes came as a result of the realization by those states of 
Sudan's firm stands toward respecting the sovereignty of states, 
and noninterference in their internal affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

