<H3> <TI>   MKO Claims Responsibility for 15 Jun Blast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MKO Claims Responsibility for 15 Jun Blast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706092994 Tehran IRNA in English 0912 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 27, IRNA -- The terrorist Mojahedin-e 
Khalq Organization (MKO) claimed responsibility for a bomb blast 
at a military center in northern Iran on June 15, reported the 
Iraq-based MKO radio station Monday [27 June]. Officials have 
not so far confirmed the claim but an informed source said that 
the MKO has made the claim in order to project the country as 
insecure. 
  The MKO also followed the same objective in the Mashhad bomb 
blast, he said. 
Twenty-six pilgrims were martyred and 170 others injured when a 
bomb went off at the holy shrine of Imam Reza (as) [peace be 
upon him] on June 20. He said that by spreading rumors about 
attacks on military centres, the terrorist MKO try to pretend 
that their terrorist attacks are focussed on military centres 
and not social meetings. 
  The claim is made at a time when security forces have 
collected documents and evidences on the involvement of the MKO 
in the bomb blast at the holy shrine of Imam Reza (as). The 
Information Ministry has published a facial sketch of Mahdi 
Nahvi, a member of the terrorist MKO who was involved in Mashhad 
bomb blast and called on the nation to introduce him to security 
forces. 

</TEXT>

