<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russians To Help Operate Nuclear Power Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russians To Help Operate Nuclear Power Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606135794 Tehran IRNA in English 1225 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bushehr, June 16, IRNA -- Preparations have been 
made to complete Iran's nuclear power plant in Bushehr in 
cooperation with Russian experts, deputy chief of the plant Mr. 
Khabir has said. 
  He said that Russian experts were finishing their technical 
studies on the power plant and it was predicted to become 
operational by the end of the second five-year development plan. 
  Russian experts will also set up a gas power station 
adjacent 
to the nuclear power plant in Bushehr, he said, but did not 
mention the capacity of the proposed plant or when the project 
would begin. 
  Khabir said that once operational, the nuclear power plant 
of 
Bushehr would provide the country with one seventh of its needed 
electricity. 
  Construction work on Bushehr's nuclear power plant started 
in 
1974 under a German mark 7.8 billion contract with two German 
companies. By the end of 1978, 80 percent of the first reactor 
and 60 percent of the second reactor of the plant were built. 
  During the 1980-88 Iraqi imposed war, Iraqi planes bombed 
the 
power plant 10 times, killing 12 staff members of the plant and 
inflicting heavy losses on it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

