<H3> <TI>   Government-Opposition Military Clashes Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government-Opposition Military Clashes Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Fierce Battles Reported </H4>

<F P=102> NC2506045494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2506045494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rival groups in Afghanistan resumed fierce battles 
in Kabul this morning. Our correspondent Darestani reports from 
Kabul: 
  [Darestani] Forces of the two conflicting sides in 
Afghanistan started severe battles in the southern areas of 
Kabul city this morning. In the battles, which are continuing, 
the two sides fired rockets and mortars at each other's 
positions, and fighter jets of President Borhanoddin Rabbani's 
government bombed the joint positions of Prime Minister 
Golboddin Hekmatyar and General Dostam in the south and 
southeast Kabul several times. 
  Severe street clashes have taken place along several lines 
of 
contact of the conflicting forces in the southern part of Kabul 
city and the forces loyal to the president are especially trying 
to infiltrate the positions of the other side. 
  Although hospital sources in Kabul have not published the 
causality figures of this battle, prolonged honking by cars 
carrying the wounded to the hospitals speak of the high number 
of casualties. 
  The severe clashes in Kabul are taking place at a time when, 
according to the decisions reached by the leaders of jehadi 
parties in Jalalabad and Islamabad, only four days are left 
before the expiration of Borhanoddin Rabbani's presidential 
term. His opponents--namely Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar, 
National Salvation Front leader Sebghatollah Mojaddedi, who was 
also the first president of the mojahedin government, as well as 
representatives of General Dostam--have gathered in Jalalabad to 
discuss the formation and institution of a government based 
outside Kabul. 
  This is the Voice and Vision of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran, 
Kabul. 

</TEXT>

