<H3> <TI>   Vice President Urges Foreign Mediation To End Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice President Urges Foreign Mediation To End Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606154494 Tehran IRNA in English 1456 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, June 26, IRNA -- Afghan Vice-President 
Molawi Mohammad Nabi Mohammadi has called for mediation of 
foreign peace missions to end the current infighting in 
Afghanistan. 
  According to a press release, the leader of Afghanistan's 
Harakat-e Enqelab-e Eslami [Islamic Revolution Movement of 
Afghanistan], also warned that if the current situation 
prevailed, the country would never see peace and tranquility 
again and would eventually fall into the hands of colonialism. 
  He accused foreign powers of involvement in the Afghan 
crisis 
and of pushing the country towards destruction in order to 
achieve their own goals. 
  The Afghan vice president urged leaders of all Afghan 
mujahideen groups to sit at the negotiating table and resolve 
their dispute through peaceful means. 

</TEXT>

