<H3> <TI>   Further on Musa Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Musa Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2606100994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0910 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2606100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Jun (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
described as a very good and positive step Sanaa's decision to 
observe a cease-fire as of midnight last night. It is important 
to respect the cease-fire in a strict way because it represents 
the right step toward resolving the crisis, Musa said. 
  Commenting on the postponement of the Damascus Declaration 
meeting, originally scheduled for Tuesday [28 June], Musa said 
that the postponement occurred due to certain obligations of 
some foreign ministers of the Damascus Declaration's signatory 
countries. 

</TEXT>

