<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Receives Saudi Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Receives Saudi Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2606082194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0731 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2606082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Jun (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
received a message from his Saudi counterpart, Prince Sa'ud 
al-Faysal, concerning current regional affairs. 'Abd-al-Rahman 
Mansuri, under secretary at the Saudi Foreign Ministry, 
delivered the message to Minister Musa today. 
  Commenting on Sanaa's announcement of a cease-fire in Yemen, 
Mansuri said: We hope that the cease-fire in Yemen will hold. 
Saudi Arabia wants to see the internecine bloodletting end. 

