<H3> <TI>   Barzani-Talabani `Civil War' Said Expected To Erupt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Barzani-Talabani `Civil War' Said Expected To Erupt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606131394 Baghdad INA in English 1100 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2606131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Northern Iraq, June 25 (INA)--Developments of the 
Barzani-Talabani cliques fighting in northern Iraq warn of a 
bloody civil war to erupt in the short run. 
  Nashirvan Mustafa, an aide of Jalal Talabani uncovered that 
eight brigades affiliated to the Kurdistani National Union were 
preparing to thrust the Barzani headquarters in the resort of 
Salah-al-Din. 
  Bitter differences roused between the two parties over the 
pro-Barzani clique reluctance to share by halves the Talabanis a 
sum of ID 750 million [Iraqi dinars] taken as customs tax from 
the individuals, cars and trucks passing through the Kurdistani 
area crossing the Iraqi-Turkish borders, Mustafa clarified. 

</TEXT>

