<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Reports Bomb Attacks on Targets in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Reports Bomb Attacks on Targets in Baghdad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2506165994 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2506165994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to yesterday's issue of the newspaper 
AL-MU'TAMAR [Congress], three explosions have occurred in 
Baghdad, burning a poster showing Saddam Husayn, causing severe 
damage to a ruling party office, and damaging an office 
belonging to the Iraqi National Assembly in the city's 
al-Thawrah suburb. 
  Iraqi opposition sources told AL-MU'TAMAR that the bombings 
were carried out by opposition fighters. The sources added that 
the regime's security forces were unable to harm these fighters. 
  The security situation in Baghdad and its suburbs is 
disorganized to an unprecedented degree. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

