<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hariri: Fight Against Occupation To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Hariri: Fight Against Occupation To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406195394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 24 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2406195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri has affirmed that 
liberating our country from the Israeli occupation continues to 
be our firm objective. It is also one of the first objectives 
of the Arab movements. He said: We cling to liberation, which 
also means that we cling to the ancient principles of our nation 
and the goals for which we have struggled. Prime Minister 
al-Hariri noted that the recent government action regarding the 
nationality law constitutes a pillar for national accord, 
justice, and the restoral of the government to its citizens. He 
affirmed that the crucial stage we are in requires us to rise to 
the level of national duty. 
  Prime Minister al-Hariri made these statements during a 
dinner party held this evening at the Summerland Hotel at the 
beginning of celebrations for the fiftieth anniversary of the 
Arab Cultural Club. A number of ministers, deputies, and 
political and cultural figures attended the celebration. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

