<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin To Study Curtailing PLO Actions in Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin To Study Curtailing PLO Actions in Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2406173894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 24 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2406173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin will summon additional 
deliberations on how to curtail PLO efforts to create political 
facts in Jerusalem. Today's meeting on the issue lasted two 
hours and was attended by the prime minister, the foreign 
minister, the police minister, the police chief, the attorney 
general, the Foreign Ministry's legal adviser, and the Shin Bet 
head. Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that there 
is no plan to initiate a comprehensive legislation on the issue, 
but to deal with each case independently. Among steps 
considered are moves to prevent problematic visits to Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

