<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Jerusalem, Palestinian Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Discusses Jerusalem, Palestinian Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2606140594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 26 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2606140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In addition to the Shamgar Commission report, 
another issue raised in today's cabinet meeting was that of 
Jerusalem, following the prime minister's remarks regarding the 
possibility of the PLO chairman's visiting the city. Minister 
Shetrit spoke about the need to intensify building activity in 
Jerusalem, but the prime minister noted the legal problems 
involved in land confiscation. Minister Bar'am urged that 
Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert not be left out of the picture in 
order to avoid playing into the hands of the extremists in the 
city. Police Minister Shahal complained that Olmert routinely 
fails to appear at meetings of the subcommittee on security 
affairs -- which operates in the framework of the Ministerial 
Committee on Jerusalem Affairs -- but rather sends a different 
representative on his behalf each time. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that the 
ministers were told that those running the autonomy are 
attempting to spread their authority beyond the regions of Gaza 
and Jericho, and efforts are being made to stop this. 
  The ministers also dealt with the tough living conditions of 
foreign workers in Israel. Minister Peres said it was a mistake 
to bring in workers from abroad. Ministers Peres and Shohat 
criticized Minister Shetrit for encroaching on their ministerial 
spheres. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

