<F P=100> Mauritania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Sends Medical Team to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Sends Medical Team to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2606150094 Paris AFP in French 1001 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2606150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nouakchott, 26 Jun (AFP) -- The Mauritanian 
Government yesterday sent a medical team to Rwanda to support 
French intervention in that country, the MAURITANIAN NEWS AGENCY 
(AMI) reported today. 
  This decision was made by the Nouakchott government "to 
alleviate the sufferings of the people who are victims of the 
Rwandan civil war," AMI said. The news agency did not, however, 
say how many people are on that medical team. 
  This is the first time Mauritania is intervening in an 
outside conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

