<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government-Opposition Military Clashes Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government-Opposition Military Clashes Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Dostam Militia Shells Kabul </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406164494 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During last night and today the Golboddin-Dostam 
militia fired 255 rockets and shells at Kabul city. A Kabul 
garrison source reported to BIA that the attacks martyred three 
defenseless citizens and injured (?24) others. Those injured 
were transferred to various hospitals. A number of houses were 
also destroyed. 

</TEXT>

