<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin, Peres To Meet 'Arafat in Paris 6 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin, Peres To Meet 'Arafat in Paris 6 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2506112494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 25 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2506112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres will meet PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat on 6 July in 
Paris. The three will be there to receive a special UNESCO 
award. During the meeting, political discussions will be held 
on, among other things, the coming stages of the political 
process. 
  Our correspondent notes that several days later, another 
meeting of the donor countries will be held in Paris, and 
'Arafat is expected to attend this meeting as well. Hence, it 
is assumed that 'Arafat will not arrive in Jericho and Gaza 
before mid-July. U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher is 
also expected in the region at that time. 

</TEXT>

