<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    16 Killed, 45 Wounded in Aden 26 Jun </H4>

<F P=102> NC2606134394 Paris AFP in English 1302 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2606134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 26 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni forces 
killed 16 civilians, including four children, and wounded 45 in 
heavy shelling of the southern port city of Aden Sunday [26 
June], hospital workers said here. 
  The four children died when Katyusha rockets slammed into 
the 
al-Tawahi district near the port. Twenty civilians were wounded 
in the same attack, workers at the Basuhayb military hospital 
said. 
  One of the rockets damaged a house and another exploded near 
a school sheltering displaced people. 
  Earlier workers at the Al-Jumhuriyah hospital said 12 dead 
civilians and 25 wounded had been admitted during the 
bombardment Sunday. 
  Fierce fighting resumed at dawn, shattering a ceasefire 
announced by the Sanaa authorities, and northern troops advanced 
into the western suburbs, seizing the Hiswah power station and 
Radio Aden buildings on the coast road. 

</TEXT>

