  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 27 (AFP) -- At least eight 
southern Yemeni soldiers were killed and 69 wounded on Monday 
[27 June] in a battle to repulse a northern advance into Aden's 
western suburbs, hospital officials said. 
  Southern artillery gunners pounded northern forces in a bid 
to dislodge them from positions around the power station at 
Hiswah and Aden Radio station, about 10 kilometers (six miles) 
west of the city. 

