<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Southern Troops Repulse Attack </H4>

<F P=102> LD2706084294 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0739 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, 27 Jun -- Fierce artillery and tank 
fighting continued between northern and southern troops on all 
fronts yesterday night and this morning. 
  A southern military communique said that northern troops, 
after being reinforced, this morning tried to attack Aden's 
defenses using large forces of tanks and heavy artillery. 
  The communique added that the southern fighters repulsed the 
northern attack with the help of air and naval forces and 
managed to drive back the northern troops. 
  The southern military communique made clear that over nine 
northern tanks were destroyed, three katyusha launchers were 
burned, five field cannons were seized, and over 50 soldiers, 
most of them young, were killed. 
  The communique said that battles around Aden are still 
raging, and that from dawn till 0900 today the residential 
quarters of the city faced intensified shelling. Fierce 
fighting erupted between northern and southern troops in and 
around Aden, with each side accusing the other of violating the 
cease-fire. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

