<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Source' on `Large-Scale' Attack by North </H4>

<F P=102> NC2706092094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0755 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 27 Jun (MENA) -- A Yemeni military source in 
Aden has stated that the northern forces resumed their attempts 
early this morning to advance toward Aden using every kind of 
weapon, including aircraft, and backed by fresh reinforcements 
brought to the various fronts. This large-scale attack on Aden 
took place a few hours after Sanaa made the sixth false 
cease-fire declaration and was accompanied by fierce rocket, 
artillery, and air bombardment against residential areas and 
vital economic installations in Aden. Yesterday's bombardment, 
which extended to schools, mosques, and kindergartens, left at 
least 75 civilians dead, most of them children and women, and 
over 150 others wounded. 
  The ADEN NEWS AGENCY said the armed forces defending Aden 
repulsed the attack and inflicted heavy losses on the forces of 
the ruling military regime in Sanaa. But this regime cares 
about nothing. It does not care about the losses its forces are 
suffering daily. It does not care about the hundreds, even 
thousands, of innocent civilian victims who fall as a result of 
its forces' indiscriminate shelling of Aden. It does not care 
about the appeals made by the local, Arab, and international 
public and the resolutions, appeals, and warnings of 
international legitimacy and the leaders of the fraternal and 
friendly countries, including the latest strong warning to the 
Sanaa regime by the U.S. State Department. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

