<H3> <TI>   National Defense Council Announces New Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Defense Council Announces New Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606050094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2606050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Defense Council met yesterday under the 
chairmanship of brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council and supreme commander of 
the Armed Forces. The Council discussed several issues and 
national developments on the political, military, security, and 
economic levels and adopted the appropriate decisions. 
  The National Defense Council reiterated that the Republic of 
Yemen is committed to UN Security Council Resolution 924 and is 
responsive to all the good efforts seeking an entrenchment of 
the cease-fire which the rebels who broke away from legitimacy 
violated every time with the aim of internationalizing the 
Yemeni crisis. 
  The Council stressed that the authorities in the Republic of 
Yemen and all units of the Yemeni Armed Forces--forces of unity 
and constitutional legitimacy--are very eager to safeguard and 
spare the blood of civilians in the suburbs of brave Aden and in 
all Yemeni cities and governorates because this is part of their 
national responsibility. 
  In response to the call made by UN Secretary General Dr. 
Butrus-Ghali yesterday; in order to give the rebels a new chance 
to stop fighting and end their rebellion; and in response to all 
good efforts by the brothers and friends to cease fire and solve 
the Yemeni problem through peaceful dialogue within the 
framework of the Republic of Yemen by maintaining unity and 
respecting the constitutional legitimacy; the National Defense 
Council announced a new initiative to entrench the cease-fire as 
of 2400 yesterday, Saturday [2100 GMT on 25 June]. The U.S. and 
French military attaches in the Republic of Yemen will directly 
supervise the cease-fire until the other members of the joint 
military committee arrive. This initiative is a proof of 
credibility and a confirmation of the extent of the Republic of 
Yemen's desire to abide by UN Security Council Resolution 924 in 
letter and spirit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-37961 </DOCNO>
