<H3> <TI>   `Rebels' Held Responsible for Rejection </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Rebels' Held Responsible for Rejection </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606130594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2606130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has stated that the rebels who 
broke away from legitimacy have refused to accept the principles 
that the National Defense Council declared yesterday to observe 
a cease-fire for the sixth time as of 2400 last night, Saturday, 
under the supervision of the U.S. and French military attaches 
in the Republic of Yemen and other members of the joint military 
committee. The initiative was in abidance by UN Security Council 
Resolution 924 and in response to the UN secretary general's 
appeal and the good efforts of brothers and friends. 
  The source said that the outlawed rebels have violated the 
cease-fire, continuing their aggression against the units of our 
Armed Forces--the forces of unity and legitimacy--in Aden and 
Hadhramaut. Since the early hours of this morning, they have 
been subjecting our troops to artillery shelling and launching 
raids against the positions of our Armed Forces, despite the 
full abidance of the forces of unity and legitimacy by 
yesterday's announcement by National Defense Council. The 
source held the separatist rebels responsible for the rejection 
of the new cease-fire initiative, their continued aggression 
against the citizens and our Armed Forces, their failure to 
respond to the UN secretary general's appeal and the good 
efforts of brothers and friends to secure a cease-fire and 
resolve the Yemeni problem through peaceful dialogue within the 
framework of the Republic of Yemen, maintaining unity, and 
respect for the constitutional legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

