<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-'Attar Briefs Envoys on Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-'Attar Briefs Envoys on Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606145094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1400 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2606145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Acting Prime Minister Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar 
met at noon today with the Russian, UK, U.S., and Chinese 
ambassadors, as well as the French charge d'affaires, the UN 
resident representative, and the Red Cross representative in the 
Republic of Yemen. He briefed them on the situation resulting 
from the rebels' cease-fire violations. He urged their 
countries to announce a clear stance condemning these acts. 

</TEXT>

