<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   KUNA Reports North Violates Declared Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KUNA Reports North Violates Declared Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606073094 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0620 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, 26 June -- Northern Yemeni troops resumed 
their artillery shelling of Aden in the south this morning, thus 
breaching the six-hour long cease-fire declared last night. The 
Yemeni news agency Aden quoted a responsible source at the 
Defense Ministry in the self-declared Democratic Republic of 
Yemen as saying: Northern troops resumed their artillery 
shelling of vital economic targets in Aden at 0615 local time. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

