<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Disturbed' by State Department Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government `Disturbed' by State Department Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2506052194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2506052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has said the Republic of Yemen 
is fully committed to the UN Security Council's call for a 
cease-fire, holding the forces rebelling against the legitimate 
authority fully responsible for the continued cease-fire 
violations. The source said that through their cease-fire 
violations, those forces are jeopardizing innocent citizens' 
lives and seeking to destroy vital and strategic institutions 
and installations throughout the Republic. 
  Referring to the wicked objectives the rebels seek to 
achieve 
through continued military operations, despite the state's 
genuine commitment and practical initiatives in this regard, the 
source explained that the rebels want to internationalize the 
issue in the service of treasonous stands. 
  Meanwhile, the responsible source said the Government of the 
Republic of Yemen is amazed and disturbed by the U.S. State 
Department's official spokesman's statement, which is not based 
on what is actually taking place on the ground. The source said 
the legitimate forces have, in practice, proved their commitment 
to the UN Security Council resolution and that the rebels are 
taking advantage of this commitment to attack legitimate forces 
with all their weapons, something which is testified to by their 
military statements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

