<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Iryani Cited on Talks With U.S. Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Iryani Cited on Talks With U.S. Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606071994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2606071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, minister of 
planning and development, currently in Washington, said that 
during his visit to the United States, he met with [name 
indistinct], the assistant U.S. secretary of state, and the 
National Security Council adviser on the Middle East. In a 
statement to the SABA' news agency, al-Iryani said that he 
discussed with U.S. officials several topics related to the 
cease-fire within the framework of UN Security Council 
Resolution 924 which is based on the fact that legitimacy 
belongs to the Republic of Yemen and that nothing else is 
legitimate. 
  Al-Iryani said that Resolution 924 was the key to all 
discussions. He said everybody was eager to realize a 
cease-fire, noting that the National Defense Council's 
cease-fire declaration represents a very important step which 
affirms the credibility of the Republic of Yemen Government's 
commitment to implementing the Security Council resolution. 

</TEXT>

