<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Returns From Qatar Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister Returns From Qatar Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2406184294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2406184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister brother 'Abd-al-Wahhab 
al-Anisi returned to Sanaa from Doha this evening at the end of 
a visit that lasted several days during which he held talks with 
officials in the sisterly State of Qatar dealing with bilateral 
relations and developments in the Yemeni arena. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', the brother 
deputy prime minister said his visit to Doha came within the 
framework of continuous contacts and coordination between the 
Republic of Yemen and the State of Qatar in the interest of the 
fraternal state and the Arab and Islamic nations. 
  He added that he conveyed the greetings and appreciation of 
the political leadership and the Yemeni people to the leadership 
of the State of Qatar and its fraternal people. He hailed the 
principled and firm Qatari support for unity and legitimacy, and 
hoped that Qatar will be an example for other Gulf Cooperation 
Council states in particular, and Arab and world countries in 
general in its support for right and the Yemeni people's will. 
  Concluding his statement, the brother deputy prime minister 
stressed that the Yemeni people will not forget the principled 
support for it during the current critical circumstances. 

</TEXT>

