<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Parties To Submit Initiative To End War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Parties To Submit Initiative To End War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2506210094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2020 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2506210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 25 Jun (MENA) -- Informed sources in Sanaa 
have told MENA's correspondent that Yemeni opposition parties 
will submit an initiative to stop the grinding war that has 
entered its eighth week between rival sides in Yemen. 
  These sources explained that the initiative calls for an 
immediate cease-fire, an unconditional dialogue, cancellation of 
all resolutions and measures that have resulted from the war and 
from the declaration of session, and for compliance with the 
Pledge and Accord Document as a basis for dialogue. 
  The initiative also calls for forming a military committee 
comprising of all the political forces to supervise the 
cease-fire. It notes that resuming dialogue is the only way out 
of the Yemeni crisis and the only way to protect Yemen's unity. 
  Yemeni sources affirmed that the initiative enjoys the 
interest of Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and the Yemeni 
Socialist Party's unionist leaders. 
  The Yemeni opposition parties include the Nationalist Forces 
Federation and the National Grouping of Opposition, which is 
comprised of the Right Party, the Yemeni Unionist Group, the 
League of the Sons of Yemen, the Nasirite Unionist Organization, 
the National Democratic Front, the Arab Socialist Ba'th 
Party--Yemen's branch, the Democratic September Organization, 
and the Nasirite Popular Reform Party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

