<H3> <TI>   Committee Formed To Seek Expatriate Donations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Formed To Seek Expatriate Donations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2706090194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2706090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The higher committee for receiving donations met 
yesterday under Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zindani, Presidential 
Council member and the committee's chairman. The committee 
members discussed a number of issues on the committee's agenda 
which aim at activating the higher committee's work and 
expanding its activity outside the homeland in a bid to allow 
our expatriate citizens to join in the honor of participating in 
the popular move to support the efforts to defend unity and 
constitutional legitimacy. In order to achieve that goal, the 
higher committee for receiving donations set up a committee to 
contact the brother expatriates in sisterly and friendly states. 
  In a related development, Brother Judge Hamid al-Hitar, 
member of the higher committee for receiving donations and head 
of the health care committee, said in statements to the Yemeni 
News Agency, SABA', that a medical convoy yesterday left for the 
governorates of al-Bayda' and Abyan, with a shipment of 
medicines and supplies needed by the hospitals in the two 
governorates to enable them to offer medical services and full 
health care. 

</TEXT>

