<F P=100> Arabian Peninsula </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Says Recognition a `Matter of Time' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says Recognition a `Matter of Time' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2406220094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2040 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2406220094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2040 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj, foreign 
affairs minister of the Democratic Republic of Yemen, said 
recognizing the Democratic Republic of Yemen has become a matter 
of time, and was neither a difficult, nor an impossible matter. 
  In an interview with the Lebanese AL-ANWAR, Brother 
'Abdallah 
al-Asnaj expected that recognizing the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen could take place in a few days, not weeks. 
  Brother al-Asnaj accused the rulers of Sanaa of waging a 
barbaric war against the southerners with the aim of occupying 
the south. 

</TEXT>

