<H3> <TI>   Comments on Cease-fire `Initiative' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on Cease-fire `Initiative' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706092694 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0803 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] London, 27 Jun -- In an interview published here 
today, a prominent southern Yemeni official affirmed: "The issue 
of a cease-fire is no longer a Yemeni issue but an international 
one according to UN Security Council Resolution No. 924." 
  Staff Brigadier Haytham Qasim Tahir, appointed as Defense 
Minister in the Democratic Republic of Yemen, which was 
unilaterally announced in south Yemen on 20 May, told Al-SHARQ 
AL-AWSAT in a telephone interview: "We have presented an 
initiative to form an international observer team to monitor 
implementation of the cease-fire and the withdrawal of northern 
troops to their position prior to the eruption of the fighting." 
He stressed he would "Not give up one inch of the lands of the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen." 
  He described human, weapons and equipment losses as being 
"small and limited among the military circles in the southern 
army. As for the civilians, the losses are great because the 
battles took place on our lands and because northern troops 
launched a deliberate random and barbaric missile, air and 
artillery attacks on towns and villages, including the capital 
Aden, which caused the death and wounding of hundreds of 
defenseless and innocent people." 

</TEXT>

