<H3> <TI>   `Source' Urges International Sanctions on North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Urges International Sanctions on North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606093494 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0844 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, 26 Jun -- A responsible source in Aden 
today accused the "rulers of Sanaa of violating the cease-fire 
they announced last night." At the same time, he called on the 
international community to adopt sanctions on the northern side 
in Yemen for continuing to violate the cease-fire. 
  In a statement to KUNA here today, the source said that the 
northern forces have shelled the residential areas of 
al-Mansurah, Shaykh 'Uthman, and Khormaksar this morning, and 
pointed out the death and wounding of numerous people. 
  The source called on the UN Security Council to adopt 
sanctions against Sanaa for continuing to violate the cease-fire. 
  The northern artillery bombardment has resumed at an earlier 
hour this morning thereby putting an end to a cease-fire that 
lasted for few hours when Sanaa announced it would adhere to it 
from midnight last night. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

