<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    South Claims Successes </H4>

<F P=102> EA2406153094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1230 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2406153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1230 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by "a responsible source at the Ministry </F>
of Defense of the Democratic Republic of Yemen"; place and date 
not given] 
  [Text] The forces of the ruling military regime in Sanaa 
have been continuing since yesterday morning [words indistinct] 
and continued their artillery and rocket attacks [words 
indistinct] and residential quarters in the city of Aden [words 
indistinct]. 
  Yesterday the ruling military regime of Sanaa initiated 
battles around Aden by means of its (?brutal) forces and used 
all kinds of destructive weapons. However, our Armed Forces and 
the masses of our people were lying in wait for the brutal 
enemy. They engaged the enemy with rare courage and legendary 
steadfastness and inflicted on the invading and aggressive 
forces crushing blows. 
  They prevented the advance of the enemy forces and inflicted 
on them the following losses: the destruction of 25 tanks; 12 
manned military vehicles, as well as other weaponry and 
equipment. They seized seven tanks. The enemy also suffered 
hundreds of dead and wounded. 
  One of those taken prisoner by our forces said that the 
commanders of the destructive war against our people told them 
that the first commander of a tank who manages to enter Aden 
will be appointed governor of Aden. He also said other things 
which we do not need to talk about now. 
  This morning the forces of the ruling military regime in 
Sanaa resumed their aggressive operations and their repeated 
attempts at attacks. The battles are still continuing. The 
morale of our forces is high and their confidence in victory is 
unlimited. God is great. 

</TEXT>

