<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th, Sarid: Jerusalem Left for Final Status Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th, Sarid: Jerusalem Left for Final Status Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2806084394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2806084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nabil Sha'th says that although the Palestinians 
have always emphasized their conviction that Jerusalem is the 
capital of the Palestinian state, the Jerusalem issue will be 
discussed only at the permanent status negotiations. In this, 
he was reacting to the Fatah-Tunis announcement that its 
autonomy elections campaign will focus on the struggle to 
preserve East Jerusalem's Arab character. 
  Minister Yosi Sarid noted that Jerusalem is not included in 
the autonomy and, as agreed, the discussions on its status will 
be conducted only during the permanent status talks. 
  Minister Sarid, Major General Dani Rothschild, and Nabil 
Sha'th met this morning at the joint command near the Erez 
checkpoint. Our correspondent Moti Amir adds that Minister 
Nabil Sha'th is now in a meeting with Maj. Gen. Dani Rothschild. 
The meeting marks the start of the negotiations on the second 
stage of the autonomy agreements. 
  As for Yasir 'Arafat's visit to the self-rule territory, 
Nabil Sha'th said the visit will take place after the 
Palestinian Authority imposes its control on all spheres of 
life. Minister Sarid added that the date of the visit will 
apparently be coordinated at the Rabin-Peres-'Arafat meeting in 
Paris. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

