<F P=100> Islamic Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   ICO Holds Talks With Afghan Leaders in Islamabad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ICO Holds Talks With Afghan Leaders in Islamabad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706220994 Riyadh SPA in English 2019 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, June 27, SPA -- The delegation of the 
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) [ICO] started 
intensive talks with the representatives of the Afghan leaders 
in Islamabad on the on-going crisis in the country and the 
escalated situation and the difficult position being faced by 
the government which was formed on bases of the Afghan consensus 
following the Islamabad and Makkah accords and subsequent 
agreements. 
  A statement issued by the OIC said the delegation has 
started 
talks with the Afghan political leaders and representatives of 
the Government of Pakistan including Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, the 
foreign minister. 
  The statement said the secretary general of the OIC is 
planning to visit the region early next month to meet with the 
leaders of various factions and try to find an agreement for 
ceasefire and refreshment of Afghan political, economic and 
social structures. 
  The secretary general sent separate messages to various 
factions, calling on them to back the efforts being made by the 
OIC to establish peace and stability in Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

