<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reactions to Detainees Issue Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reactions to Detainees Issue Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706212194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2706212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Muhammad Bishqar from Beirut] </F>
  [Text] In the name of God, the compassionate, the merciful. 
The issue of the Palestinian detainees in the jails of the 
Zionist occupation authorities continues to be the focus of 
public activity in occupied Palestine. A general strike was 
observed today in the West Bank, occupied Jerusalem, and the two 
Palestinian autonomous areas of Gaza and Jericho to show 
solidarity with thousands of Palestinian detainees who reject 
the Zionist conditions for their release. They have been on a 
hunger strike since last week. 
  Today's strike was accompanied by massive demonstrations in 
West Bank towns and refugee camps and sit-ins in front of the 
offices of the International Committee of the Red Cross [ICRC] 
in Gaza and Jericho. The protesters called for the detainees' 
unconditional release and criticized the PLO leadership's method 
of handling the detainee issue. 
  Hundreds of Palestinian detainees in the Zionist jail in 
Nabulus have also assailed the PLO leadership. In a statement 
today, they leveled sharp criticisms at Yasir 'Arafat's 
leadership style which exploits the detainee issue as a 
bargaining chip. The statement affirmed that the detainees will 
persist in refusing to sign declarations of support for the 
peace agreement with the enemy or promise to halt the intifadah 
as a condition for their release. 
  Ahmad Jibril's Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] distributed a leaflet in the 
West Bank blaming 'Arafat's leadership for the continued 
suffering of thousands of Palestinian detainees in the enemy's 
jails. The PFLP-GC called on the Palestinian people to continue 
their intifadah and express solidarity with the detainees by 
demonstrating and holding sit-ins. 
  The Forces of the Palestinian Alliance that comprise the 10 
factions opposed to the peace agreement with the enemy organized 
a sit-in today for the second day running in front of the ICRC 
office in Damascus to declare solidarity with the detainees. 
The protesters delivered a message to ICRC officials, to be 
forwarded to the United Nations, calling for the prompt and 
unconditional release of all Palestinian prisoners in Israeli 
jails regardless of their political affiliations. 
  Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general of the Democratic Front 
for the Liberation of Palestine, declared in the Syrian capital 
today that the Palestinian detainee issue is the focus of a 
fresh popular resurgence inside and outside occupied Palestine. 
Hawatimah emphasized that the Palestinians are confident now 
that the peace agreement between the PLO and the Zionist enemy 
does not serve their interests and cannot survive because of the 
complex problems hindering its implementation, particularly in 
connection with the issues of Jerusalem, the detainees, and 
Palestinian human rights. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38010 </DOCNO>
