<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Ministers Debate Compensation for Gulf War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Ministers Debate Compensation for Gulf War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606163894 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1511 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait, 26 Jun -- The Kuwaiti ministerial council 
held its weekly meeting today under the chairmanship of Sa'd 
al-'Abdallah al-Salim al-Sabah, heir apparent and prime 
minister, and discussed a number of important issues. 
  'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dakhil, minister of state for cabinet 
affairs and minister of planning, said that the council issued a 
resolution appointing the Ministry of Finance and the General 
Commission for Compensations to prepare a system of rules and 
procedures according to which compensation would be paid for the 
damage and losses resulting from the Iraqi aggression against 
the State of Kuwait, in keeping with UN resolutions regarding 
the payment of the first installment of compensation. 
  He added that the council entrusted the compensation 
commission with the disbursement of compensation and with 
following up with the UN committee with regard to measures 
required to pay those Kuwaitis and others who suffered damage. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

