<H3> <TI>   Chamber of Commerce Denies Members Visited Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chamber of Commerce Denies Members Visited Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2406160994 Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM in Arabic 21 Jun 94 pp 
1, 21 </F>

<F P=103> JN2406160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahd al-'Arrak] </F>
  [Text] Informed sources of the Chamber of Commerce and 
Industry have denied that any of its members recently paid a 
working visit to Israel along with a delegation of Gulf 
businessmen. 
  These sources told AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM that what has been 
published recently about a visit by businessmen from the Gulf 
Cooperation Council to Tel Aviv last week may be correct, but 
not a single Kuwaiti businessman participated in this visit. 
  It is noteworthy that the board chairman of the Egyptian 
Airlines Company, ZAS [name as published], has recently stated 
that his company had carried businessmen from the Gulf states to 
Tel Aviv to discuss spheres of cooperation and joint 
opportunities in light of peace prospects in the region. 

</TEXT>

