<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK's Heseltine Holds Briefing on Purpose of Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK's Heseltine Holds Briefing on Purpose of Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706211094 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1950 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait, 27 June (KUNA) -- Michael Heseltine, 
British president of the Board of Trade, said here today that he 
did not discuss "any new trade deals" for British companies in 
Kuwait as part of a privatization drive. 
  Heseltine told a news conference here today that his visit 
was confined to strengthening bilateral ties between the two 
countries and to present Britain's privatization experience and 
its success so that Kuwait could benefit from it. 
  He expressed his hope that British companies would be given 
more investment opportunities in Kuwait, stressing that the 
final decision belonged to the Kuwaiti Government. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

