<H3> <TI>   Ministry: Aden Citizens Free To Travel to Any Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry: Aden Citizens Free To Travel to Any Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806051794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by "a responsible source" at the Interior </F>
Ministry; place and date not given] 
  [Text] In the light of compliance with the cease-fire 
decision, and out of concern to allow the brother citizens in 
Aden to move freely and safely to other parts and governorates 
of the Republic, the Interior Ministry informs all the brother 
citizens in Aden that they can travel to any area of the 
Republic they wish, including travel to and from 'Adan al-Sughra 
[a suburb of Aden]. 
  The Interior Ministry, in cooperation with the Armed Forces, 
will provide all facilities to the brother citizens during their 
travel to and from Aden. 

</TEXT>

