<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa `Source' Denies North Cease-Fire Violation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa `Source' Denies North Cease-Fire Violation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2706113194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2706113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official Yemeni spokesman has denied rumors 
circulated by certain Gulf and foreign media that the forces of 
legitimacy violated the cease-fire. 
  In a press statement issued last night, the Yemeni spokesman 
refuted allegations by REUTER and other Gulf news agencies that 
the aircraft of the legitimate forces raided Aden suburbs where 
the rebels are deployed and targeted the drinking water storage 
tanks in the area. The spokesman said these allegations are 
fabricated, noting that the drinking water sources are 
controlled by the forces of legitimacy and not in the hands of 
the rebels. 
  The source criticized reports by the Egyptian Middle East 
News Agency, the United Arab Emirates Television, and the Kuwait 
Television that the forces of legitimacy violated the 
cease-fire. He stressed that this bias in favor of the western 
media organs serve schemes that aim only at harming Yemen and 
the unity of its people and land. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38030 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes124_j_94023" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-124 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Claims `Rebels' Breach Cease-fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Claims `Rebels' Breach Cease-fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806050894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source has stated that the gang of 
rebels has not abided by the cease-fire since it was announced 
and until now, despite its false claims that it accepted it and 
is committed to implement it. 
  The source said this rebel gang continued its treacherous 
attacks against units of the Armed Forces on the Aden axis and 
against the brother citizens and residential quarters in the 
city. The rebels used naval units and bombarded the positions 
of the forces of unity and constitutional legitimacy from the 
land and sea. They also intensified air sorties over the Armed 
Forces camps in al-Haswah, Dar Sa'd, al-Kamathri, Shaykh 
'Uthman, and other areas. 
  The source stressed that this gang, which sold itself, its 
mind, and conscience to the devil, continues its attacks, 
thinking that this will enable it to arrive at its objective of 
internationalizing the crisis of the domestic sedition which it 
flared to serve and execute its failed traitorous scheme against 
the people and their unity, security, stability. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38031 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes124_j_94024" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-124 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   South Statement Urges Intervention, Says No Surrender </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Statement Urges Intervention, Says No Surrender </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806053694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2200 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 27 Jun (MENA) -- The self-declared 
presidential council in south Yemen has called for other 
countries to intervene to stop the constant northern Yemeni 
shelling of civilians and vital institutions in Aden and what it 
termed "the brutal acts of repression by the Sanaa regime in the 
occupied areas." 
  A statement issued by the council and faxed to MENA tonight 
says: "The Sanaa regime has no respect for the resolutions and 
pleas made by the international community. It has consistently 
declared cease-fires, breached them, and blamed the southerners." 
  The statement accuses Sanaa's authorities of depriving 
Aden's 
inhabitants of water, saying that wells are the only source of 
water following the destruction of water pipes and reservoirs 
and the purification station. 
  The statement vows continuing "national resistance in the 
occupied areas" and says that the southerners refuse to 
surrender. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

