<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fierce Battles Continue to Rage Near Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fierce Battles Continue to Rage Near Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Aden Facing `Intensive Shelling' </H4>

<F P=102> LD2706123794 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden hospital sources say that 12 people were killed 
and 100 injured in shelling by north Yemeni forces in the 
northern outskirts of Aden this morning. 
  Medical sources have let it be known that four citizens were 
killed and 31 injured by northern forces' shelling of the Shaykh 
'Uthman, al Mansurah, Dar Sa'd and 'Umar al Mukhtar districts 
north of Aden. 
  REUTERS quoted south Yemeni officials as saying that more 
than 250 people were killed and hundreds injured during last 
week's Yemeni shelling of Aden. 
  A Yemeni military source said that fierce battles with tanks 
and artillery between the south and north Yemeni forces are 
continuing on all fronts and that Aden has been facing an 
intensive northern shelling of residential districts since dawn 
today. The south Yemeni military communique pointed out that 
more than nine north Yemeni tanks and three Katyusha launchers 
were burned and more than 50 soldiers were killed. 

</TEXT>

